Proportions of unsaponifiables within tree-borne seed oils are presented in 
   Table 4. ORT and JLT had the highest level of unsaponifiables in tree-borne seed oils, which seemed to be proportional to the high tocopherol level (101.98 ± 1.34 mg/100 g oil; 
   Table 2) and a high phytosterol content (479.45 ± 4.27 mg/100 g oil; 
   Table 3) of JLT. For industrial application of unsaponifiables (fat-soluble vitamins, fat-soluble pigments, and phytosterols), the study results on total oil contents of seeds will be informative.
